data.value: When working with LANGMaster courses we recommend to use a bilingual dictionary. The dictionary is directly linked with the course and includes many advanced functions:

data.name: c43671435e30484a9ca0e7f908ae066e
data.value: You can display translation of any unfamiliar word, which makes comprehension of a foreign text much easier.

data.name: 134ba3073e72470aa0431b88ce0e5b36
data.value: You can listen to the correct pronunciation of the words and phrases from the course (recorded by native speakers).

data.name: 5919a369ef80407c83d4210ec4b52ca4

data.name: 67b8b0075a0942d1939a34b747c00996
data.value: Place the mouse cursor over an unfamiliar word.

data.name: 2ec3f5f28879499fa4a1afa7f733a83a
data.value: A window with a translation and an offer of additional dictionary functions will appear.

data.name: 65e60c89ecc84b9697008b5308721221
data.value: Display the dictionary window placing the mouse cursor over a word and pressing "Ctrl+Q" or "CTRL+C".

data.name: a6c891e89fb7403f8bd8dc58f032e0d1
data.value: Listen to the correct pronunciation using the speaker icon.

data.name: 94960b0287e847ee8e87a050c1fac956

data.name: ba24cd31ffdd436c84ea4a7d474b2cab

data.name: bbc6ff1853d04f26b71d8913185c5a05
data.value: Automatic language recognition: You don’t have to worry about the direction of your translation as you work. The dictionary will automatically recognize which language the searched word comes from.

data.name: e17147e83ccf4e49b22f10f9ea41dfe2
data.value: Search course words in any form: You can translate a word regardless of its case, number, gender, or tense. For example, with the English word "went", the dictionary will correctly search the entry "go".

data.name: 939b2e6b60414d4fbb1e07d638c25313
data.value: Related links: Other links to the entry are looked up simultaneously, such as: Synonyms, phrase words, derived words, collocations, etc.
